This paper discusses the use of data mining and machine learning technology in the recommendation process, which is a common topic in the information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also focuses on the use of sequentially-ordered user-item interaction logs, which falls under the scope of sequential data analysis (cs.SI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses methodological approaches for benchmarking sequence-aware recommender systems, which could also be relevant to the cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category.
